TASK_TITLE=Fix Taskmaster routing — dispatches to Workers instead of Subtaskmasters
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=bug
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W3
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Taskmaster is sending work directly to Worker panes (e.g. 2.1) instead of routing through the Subtaskmaster (2.0). The architecture requires Taskmaster -> Subtaskmaster -> Workers. The Subtaskmaster plans, delegates, and validates. Bypassing it means no planning layer, no validation, and workers get raw unstructured instructions. Research the Taskmaster agent definition, dispatch logic, and send-keys targets to find where the routing goes wrong.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:Phase 1 Research: Dispatched to Subtaskmaster 3.0 — reading Taskmaster agent def, dispatch logic, routing targets:done\n2:W3.1: Research Taskmaster routing — read agent defs, dispatch skills, and shell send helpers to identify where routing targets are determined and why Workers get dispatched instead of Subtaskmasters:done\n3:W3.1: Implement routing fix — remove Direct Dispatch section from doey-taskmaster.md.tmpl, add routing reminder to Managed Team Spawn, regenerate templates, run compat tests:done\n4:Phase 2 Implementation: Remove Direct Dispatch section from doey-taskmaster.md.tmpl, regenerate templates:done\n5:Review Gate: Sent to Task Reviewer (1.1):done\n6:Deployment: Sent to Deployment (1.2) after review PASS:pending
